(Determine the center of rectangular object and set the center to be zero of G54)
(The initial origin must be roughly at the center of the object)

O <find-rectangle-center> sub

M5 (tunr off the spindle)
G21 (mm is machine unit)

(Rough Estimation of Size)
#<_x_lenght> = 390.000
#<_y_lenght> = 250.000
#<_z_height> = 15.000
#<_angle>    = 3.000 (degrees)

(Go to the G54 origin)
G54
G0 Z[#<_z_height>+4]

(Go to the Center and Probe Z)
G0 Z[#<_z_height>+4]
G0 X[#<_x_lenght>/2] Y[#<_y_lenght>/2]
G38.2 Z[-#<_z_height>-30] F140.0
G10 L20 P1 Z0
G0 Z5.0

(-->Probe point 1)
G0 X[#<_x_lenght>/2] Y-10.0
G0 Z-1.5

G38.2 Y10.0 F150.0
#<point1> = #5062
G0 Y-5
G0 Z5.0

(-->Probe point 2)
G0 X[#<_x_lenght>/2] Y[#<_y_lenght>+10]
G0 Z-1.5

G38.2 Y[#<_y_lenght>-10.0] F150.0
#<point2> = #5062
G0 Y[#<_y_lenght>+5]
G0 Z5.0

(-->Set the Y center)
#<y_center> = [#<point1>+[#<point2>-#<point1>]/2]
G0 Y[#<y_center>]
G10 L20 P1 Y0

(-->Probe point 3)
G0 X[#<_x_lenght>+10] Y0
G0 Z-1.5

G38.2 X[#<_x_lenght>-10] F150.0
#<point3> = #5061
G0 Z5.0

(-->Probe point 4)
G0 X-10.0 Y0
G0 Z-1.5

G38.2 X10.0 F150.0
#<point4> = #5061
G0 X-5.0
G0 Z5.0

(-->Set the X center)
#<x_center> = [#<point4>+[#<point3>-#<point4>]/2]
G0 X[#<x_center>] 
G10 L20 P1 X0

O <find-rectangle-center> endsub

M2
